Revision history for RT-Extension-QueueListCustom

1.2   2026-06-01
    - Performance: ticket count query now runs as system user, eliminating
      per-ticket ACL overhead (cold response time ~100ms, down from ~1000ms)

1.1   2026-05-22
    - Ticket count aggregation cached in session for 60 seconds
    - Reload button (↺) bypasses cache and forces a fresh DB query
    - Reduces repeated portlet load time from ~1000ms to <10ms

1.0   2026-05-22
    - First public release
    - Preferences page: status checkboxes now grouped by category (initial /
      active / inactive) in a horizontal layout
    - Preferences page: unsaved-changes indicator and Save button now appear
      in a fixed bottom bar spanning the full viewport width, always visible
      regardless of scroll position
    - Preferences page: bar appears and Save button highlights on any change,
      including Select all / Deselect all / Reset to defaults actions
    - Preferences page: sticky table headers in portlet (queue summary table)

0.04  2026-05-22
    - Lifecycle section headers are now visually highlighted with a
      colour-coded background (one distinct Bootstrap colour per lifecycle)
    - Whole header row is now the collapse/expand toggle target
    - Added screenshots to README

0.03  2026-05-21
    - Per-lifecycle queue visibility: hide individual queues per user
    - Empty-queue hiding toggle (Show empty queues preference)
    - Collapsible lifecycle sections with saved collapsed state per user
    - Drag-and-drop lifecycle ordering on preferences page (Sortable.js)
    - Manual reload button fetches fresh ticket counts via AJAX
    - Last-loaded timestamp shown at the bottom of the portlet
    - Configurable auto-refresh (2 / 5 / 10 / 20 / 60 / 120 minutes)
    - Fixed: license value in Makefile.PL (gpl2 → gpl)
    - Fixed: collapse arrow now appears before lifecycle name in portlet header
    - Added META.yml; added perl_version 5.010 requirement

0.01  2026-05-21
    - Initial release
    - Per-user, per-lifecycle status configuration via dedicated preferences page
    - Portlet shows only queues the current user has ShowTicket access to
    - Falls back to initial + active statuses when no preferences are saved
    - Gear icon links directly to the preferences page
